Describe a sport that you really like
- what it is
- how often you do it
- how you learned to do it
- explain why you like it

I would like to describe a sport that I'm really passionate about, and that's badminton. It's a fun and exciting game that
requires agility, strategic thinking and quick reflexes. It's a racquet sport played with two opposing players or two opposing pairs, who take positions on opposite halves of a rectangle court that is divided by a net. Players score points by striking a shuttlecock with their racquet so that it passes over the net and lands in their opponent's half of the court.

I try to play badminton at least once a week, usually with colleages and friends after a long day at work. We are fortunate that there is a sports complex within a walking distance from my office. There are several badminton courts inside, so it's easy to get a game in. Sometimes, I take part in (play in) several friendly tournaments to engage with new friends who share the same interest. These activities are always a lot of fun and leave memorable experiences.

I first started playing it during my school days. It was a part of our physical education curriculum. At first, I found it quite challenging. But overtime, I took a liking to the sport. Since then, it had become a regular part of my day and I tried to play it whenever I got the chance. After school, I continued playing with friends and colleagues. I even joined a local badminton club for a while, which really helped me refine my skills and strategies.

There are several reason why I enjoy playing badminton. Firstly, it is relative simple in terms of facilities to get started. Unlike some other sports that require large teams or extensive equipment, all you need is a racket, a shuttlecock, and a partner to play with. Secondly, it's a fantastic way to get exercise. It's a dynamic sport that requires a lot of jumping, running, and quick reflexes. It provides an excellent full-body workout, helps improving stamina and coordination. It's also a great cardiovascular exercise to prevent heart disease. Thirdly, it's a demanding sport that requires both physical and mentally agility. I'm really into the strategic aspect of the game, trying to outmaneuver my opponent and anticipate their moves. It's a real test of skill and strategy. Overall, badminton is the sport that I deeply enjoy. It's an enjoyable way to spend quality time with closed ones. It keeps me physically fit, mentally shape, and socially engaged. I hope to continue playing for many years to come.

