What is one benefit of playing badminton
One major benefit of playing badminton is that it improves cardiovascular system. Since it is a fast-paced sport, players have to constantly run, jump, and react quickly. These movements raise your heart rate and help your cardiovascular system work more efficiently. As a result, it strengthens the heart and improves blood circulation. In the long run, playing badminton regularly can improve endurance and overall heart health.
